    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-06-21T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-06-21T22:00:00-05:00" n="489"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4486: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul in Charge at Canton</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Huston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-22T11:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1922—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 23—11:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Wu Ting-fang<note n="57" xml:id="d489fn57">Minister of Foreign Affairs, Canton
                        Government.</note> handed over seal of office to Provincial Assembly on
                    21st. On the same day Assembly elected Chen as Provisional Governor of
                    Kwangtung. On 22nd Chen wired Wu Ting-fang asking <pb facs="0844" n="724"
                        xml:id="pg_724"/> him to persuade Sun to retire for the sake of unification.
                    Agreement between Chen’s officers and navy. The navy will request retirement Sun
                    and submit to Chen’s authority. Sun still at Whampoa. He hopes expeditionary
                    force can fight way back Canton. A few followers advising him retire. Wu
                    Ting-fang died at one this morning [of] pneumonia after brief illness.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
